                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": [
                    {
                        "start": 47,
                        "end": 50
                    }
                ]
            },
            {
                "text": "That which we have seen and heard declare we unto you, that ye also may have fellowship with us: and truly our fellowship is with the Father, and with his Son Jesus Christ.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Witness.",
                        "start": 19,
                        "end": 23
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Fellowshipping.",
                        "start": 111,
                        "end": 121
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "Moses 6:68.",
                        "start": 134,
                        "end": 140
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": [
                    {
                        "start": 122,
                        "end": 124
                    }
                ]
            },
            {
                "text": "And these things write we unto you, that your joy may be full.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Scriptures, Writing of.",
                        "start": 17,
                        "end": 22
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "This then is the message which we have heard of him, and declare unto you, that God is light, and in him is no darkness at all.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "John 8:12. TG\u00a0God, Perfection of; Light [noun].",
                        "start": 87,
                        "end": 92
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Darkness, Spiritual; Walking in Darkness.",
                        "start": 111,
                        "end": 119
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "If we say that we have fellowship with him, and walk in darkness, we lie, and do not the truth:",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Walking in Darkness.",
                        "start": 48,
                        "end": 52
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "2\u00a0Ne. 15:20.",
                        "start": 56,
                        "end": 64
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "But if we walk in the light, as he is in the light, we have fellowship one with another, and the blood of Jesus Christ his Son cleanseth us from all sin.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Walking with God.",
                        "start": 10,
                        "end": 14
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "Acts 20:28; Rev. 7:14; D&C 29:17. TG\u00a0Blood, Symbolism of.",
                        "start": 97,
                        "end": 102
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "Rev. 12:11 (10\u201312); D&C 50:28. TG\u00a0Jesus Christ, Atonement through.",
                        "start": 127,
                        "end": 136
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "If we say that we have no sin, we deceive ourselves, and the truth is not in us.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "Prov. 30:20.",
                        "start": 23,
                        "end": 25
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Sin.",
                        "start": 26,
                        "end": 29
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Lying.",
                        "start": 34,
                        "end": 41
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "If we confess our sins, he is faithful and just to forgive us our sins, and to cleanse us from all unrighteousness.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Confession; Repent.",
                        "start": 6,
                        "end": 13
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0God, Justice of; Justice.",
                        "start": 43,
                        "end": 47
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Forgive.",
                        "start": 51,
                        "end": 58
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Purification; Purity.",
                        "start": 79,
                        "end": 86
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [
                    {
